and his scalping knife off Anglesea       s hair.
The children used often to walk over with Le to
Greenbushes in the morning, spend the whole day there
with their cousin, and return with him in the evening.
But, in consideration for him, they never alluded to
the approaching wedding. They only kept their eyes and
ears open, like the sharp little foxes that they were.
One day, however, when all three were walking
through the wintry woods on their way to Greenbushes,
